      72.02,
      527.64,
      526.54,
      541.81
    ],
    "text": "possession and trafficking of drugs, which provides for a term of imprisonment of",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      549.24,
      526.36,
      563.41
    ],
    "text": "not less than seven years and not exceeding twenty years, together with a fine",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      570.84,
      526.36,
      585.01
    ],
    "text": "ranging from Rs. 100,000 to Rs. 500,000. Accordingly, we note that the law",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      592.56,
      316.85,
      606.73
    ],
    "text": "stipulates a minimum mandatory sentence.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      626.16,
      526.33,
      640.33
    ],
    "text": "It is evident that a minimum sentence is prescribed by law. However, our courts",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      647.79,
      526.34,
      661.96
    ],
    "text": "have recognized that a Trial Judge retains the discretion to determine an",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      669.51,
      526.37,
      683.68
    ],
    "text": "appropriate sentence without being bound by the minimum mandatory sentence.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      691.11,
      526.54,
      705.28
    ],
    "text": "Nevertheless, if the Judge decides to impose a sentence below the statutory",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      712.71,
      526.46,
      726.88
    ],
    "text": "minimum, such a departure must be supported by adequate and clearly stated",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      734.42,
      121.08,
      748.6
    ],
    "text": "reasons.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      781.3,
      324.89,
      805.78
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.05,
      526.52,
      86.22
    ],
    "text": "In the present case, we note that the Learned High Court Judge has failed to give",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      93.67,
      526.56,
      107.84
    ],
    "text": "reasons why he has imposed such a sentence below the minimum sentence. It is",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      115.39,
      436.25,
      129.56
    ],
    "text": "relevant to reproduce that portion of the order dated 14.02.2014.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      148.99,
      526.76,
      163.75
    ],
    "text": "\u201c\u0dad\u0dc0\u0daf \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dd9 \u0db8 \u0ddd\u0daf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d85\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dc0 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dd9 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb \u0daf\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9 \u0db8 \u0dcf\u0da7 \u0d87\u0dad\u0dad\u0dca, \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dd9 \u0db1\u0da9\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dda",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      169.75,
      526.76,
      184.51
    ],
    "text": "\u0daf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db8\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0dab\u0db8\u0dda \u0d85\u0db7\u0dd2\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dba \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0d85\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0db1\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db6\u0dc0",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      191.35,
      526.76,
      206.11
    ],
    "text": "\u0dad\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba \u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2. \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dd9 \u0dc0\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dad \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb \u0daf\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0dbb\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0daf \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca \u0d94\u0dc4\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      213.43,
      526.76,
      228.19
    ],
    "text": "\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dcf\u0da2\u0db8\u0dda \u0dba\u0dc4\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dc1\u0db8\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0da7\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0db8\u0dda\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca, \u0d94\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      234.19,
      526.76,
      248.95
    ],
    "text": "\u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0db8\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dd3 \u0dd9\u0dc0 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d85\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd3\u0dd9\u0daf \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0d94\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dda \u0da2\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0db8\u0dda \u0dc0\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dcf \u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      255.79,
      526.76,
      270.55
    ],
    "text": "\u0db6\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd3\u0dd9 \u0dd9\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d94\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0daf \u0dba\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dc5 \u0dcf \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db8\u0dd2. \u0d92 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      277.78,
      486.2,
      292.54
    ],
    "text": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb \u0daf\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db8\u0dca \u0db8\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dd9 \u0db8\u0dba\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dba \u0db6\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba \u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "IskoolaPota"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      333.46,
      526.37,
      347.63
    ],
    "text": "The central question is whether the learned High Court Judge lawfully exercised",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      355.06,
      526.71,
      369.23
    ],
    "text": "his discretion in awarding a sentence below the statutory minimum. The objective",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      376.66,
      526.36,
      390.83
    ],
    "text": "of criminal justice is to safeguard society from offenders by imposing punishment",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      398.38,
      526.39,
      412.55
    ],
    "text": "under the existing penal system. Such punishment is intended to serve as a",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      419.98,
      526.5,
      434.15
    ],
    "text": "deterrent to others from committing criminal acts. In determining sentences,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      441.58,
      526.76,
      455.75
    ],
    "text": "courts have taken into account the nature of the offence and its impact on society.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      475.32,
      530.7,
      489.49
    ],
    "text": "I am mindful of the sentiments expressed by His Lordship Basnayake ACJ in The",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.24,
      496.92,
      526.5,
      511.09
    ],
    "text": "Attorney General v. H.N. De Silva 57 NLR 121 at page 124 in the matter of",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      518.52,
      364.37,
      532.69
    ],
    "text": "assessing the sentence to be imposed for an offence.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      552.24,
      530.46,
      566.41
    ],
    "text": "\u201cIn assessing the punishment that should be passed on an offender, a Judge",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      573.84,
      530.38,
      588.01
    ],
    "text": "should consider the matter of sentence both from the point of view of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      595.44,
      530.34,
      609.61
    ],
    "text": "public and the offender. Judges are too often prone to look at the question",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      617.16,
      530.51,
      631.33
    ],
    "text": "only from the angle of the offender. A Judge should, in determining the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      638.76,
      530.33,
      652.93
    ],
    "text": "proper sentence, first consider the gravity of the offence as it appears from",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      660.39,
      530.36,
      674.56
    ],
    "text": "the nature of the act itself and should have regard to the punishment",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      681.99,
      530.71,
      696.16
    ],
    "text": "provided in the Penal Code or other statute under which the offender is",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      703.71,
      530.37,
      717.88
    ],
    "text": "charged. He should also regard the effect of the punishment as a deterrent",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      725.31,
      382.35,
      739.48
    ],
    "text": "and consider to what extent it will be effective.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      781.3,
      324.89,
      805.78
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.05,
      530.62,
      86.22
    ],
    "text": "This dictum was followed by His Lordship Gunasekara J in The Attorney General",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      71.24,
      93.67,
      305.31,
      107.84
    ],
    "text": "v. Mendis 1995 1 SLR 138 and held that;",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      127.39,
      530.4,
      141.56
    ],
    "text": "\u201cIn our view once an accused is found guilty and convicted on his own plea,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      148.99,
      530.22,
      163.16
    ],
    "text": "or after trial, the Trial Judge has a difficult function to perform. That is to",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      170.59,
      530.39,
      184.76
    ],
    "text": "decide what sentence is to be imposed on the accused who has been",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      192.31,
      530.59,
      206.48
    ],
    "text": "convicted. In doing so he has to consider the point of view of the accused on",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      213.91,
      412.83,
      228.08
    ],
    "text": "the one hand and the interest of society on the other.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      247.51,
      216.03,
      261.68
    ],
    "text": "Further held that;",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      281.26,
      530.37,
      295.43
    ],
    "text": "\u201cWe are in agreement with the observations of Basnayake, A.C.J. that",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      302.86,
      530.33,
      317.03
    ],
    "text": "whilst \"the reformation of the criminal though no doubt is an important",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      324.46,
      530.36,
      338.63
    ],
    "text": "consideration in assessing the punishment that should be passed on an",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      346.18,
      530.62,
      360.35
    ],
    "text": "offender, where the public interest or the welfare of the state outweighs the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      367.78,
      530.36,
      381.95
    ],
    "text": "previous good character, antecedents and age of the offender, that public",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.24,
      389.38,
